s our knowledge of the various properties of demonstratives, their syntactic multi-functionality, semantic feature specifications and pragmatic functions. In addition, some of the papers discuss different grammaticalization processes involving demonstratives, in particular how and from which lexical and morphosyntactic categories they originate cross-linguistically, and which semantic or pragmatic mechanisms play which role in their emergence. As such, the different contributions guide the readers on an adventurous journey into the realm of different exotic species of demonstratives, whose peculiar properties offer new exiting insights into the complex nature of demonstrative expressions themselves.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxDemonstratives. 4aDeixis. 4aDemonstrativpronomen. 4aDeterminierer. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh  aDeixis.  aDemonstratives.  aDeterminers.1 aArsenijević, Boban, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConiglio, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConiglio, Marco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCorver, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCui, Jin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiusti, Giuliana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinterwimmer, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKönig, Ekkehard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLos, Bettelou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLücking, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 